Excited with the achievement of the Federal Ministry of Works and Housing’s sports club, acting permanent secretary of the Ministry, Engineer Chukwuwike Uzo, has charged the club to sustain sporting activities. He gave the charge during the 2021 award presentation to deserving athletes and sports managers for their outstanding performance. Engineer Uzo described sports as a tool for enhancing social wellbeing and building bridges among peoples and urged staff to make sports a daily habit. He assured the club of the continued support of the Ministry, saying the Minister Babatunde Raji Fashola remains committed to the wellbeing of the staff. He also charged the sports club to sweep medals at the next edition of the Federation of Public Service Games (FESPGA). The highlight of the ceremony was the launching of the Club Magazine. In his welcome address, manager ministry of works and housing’s sports club, Comrade Fakande Ayorinde, said the club known as ‘Mighty works and Housing’ has performed excellently in various competitions of Federation of Public Service Games (FESPGA) and the leadership of the club thought it wise to celebrate the athletes who did the ministry proud. “The Sports club executives thought it wise to celebrate and honour medalists who made the proud in the just concluded 2021 FEPSGA Competition and also award some members of the club that had contributed immensely in one way or the other to the development and growth of the club. ‘Also, the launching of the maiden edition of the Ministry’s Sports Club Magazine was as a result of the unflinching support we received from the management and stakeholders,” Ayorinde said.